It will be found, when the whole of this important body of evidence is published‚ that there is scarcely a city or town in Normandy‚ Gascony‚ or such of the other provinces of France as were formerly subject to England‚ which will not be able to find its charter of incorporation, aug- mentations of its privilege& or confirmations of its fran- chises in this work. The religious communities in those countries will also obtain information of grants of land to them, exemptions from tolls and impostS, and other advantageous privileges: whilst the historians of F rance will discover many interesting documentS, some tending to the establishment or elucidation of historical facts, others proving the antiquity of many of the principal families in that kingdom: supplying a fund of original data hitherto unknown.
